						<summary>

						<p>On a stone planted in front of the temple of Mallēśvara 1(1/2) miles from the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1678, Yuva, Vaiśākha, ba. 5, Wednesday.</p>						

						<p>Records the construction of a well, a temple for Śiva (Mallēśvara) and temple for Hanumān near the well by Malli-Śeṭṭi, son of Mailavaram Basuvanna of Vichiriśeṭla-gōtra.</p>						

						</summary>
